notes: Pitfall||10mEPE|Waypoint 192||Isidro (Caca0o 2009) let me in the locked gate - didn`t recognise me at first. Walked up from 7:45-9:00 to 1200m. Traps open and bait down at 9:33. Video of Gnapto at Bait 4. 360 GigaPan (17x48) taken at ~Sift 1. Moist. Malaise trap erected at Santa Rosa at 6:30am. notes: Sift|Gnaptogenys at the colony entrance, Aphaenogaster, 2x Gnaptogenys, Myrmicinae|Traps out and bait down at 9am. Gigapan taken uphill from the creek under a fantastic canopy tree. Should be a Pachycondyla visible on the rock of the upstream direction. Temperature was 18-21C all day. Toledo birds singing after 12. 1 Agoti. Large ambulatory ponerinae and Gnaptogenys dominate here. Video of Pachycondyla, fight with bodies cut in half and lost legs, many small black Solenopsis-oids, small Pheidole colony entrance and Gnaptogenys burrowing into obscured colony entrance. 5hrs sampling. |Waypoint 38|IMG_6606.JPG|http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W0aC8tEhsvk|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/71757/|http://bit.ly/hLjiSP |https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

notes: Pitfall||We left the truck at 8:15 and it took almost exactly 1 hr to hike up to the Cima - 500m up. Traps out and bait down at 9:45. Very still, many flies and hummingbirds. Traps up at 2:30.|Waypoint 39|IMG_6611.JPG||http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/72097/|http://bit.ly/fuwb5Q|https://sites.google.com/site/acgantcollectionsfeb2011/|Worker

Tried a hand-held GigaPan using the tripod from under the darp looking uphill. Large woodpecker hung around the site most of the afternoon. Very little wind. |Waypoint 107|||http://gigapan.org/gigapans/93633|http://bit.ly/t7Gpd4|https://sites.google.com/site/acgdecemember2011

Walked Sendero del Caro until first small peak after the trail splits (I`d gone to the right). Wet at the start, but VERY dry where I sampled. Windy, sunny and the temperature rose from 24 - 27C while I was sampling. All traps down at 8:22am. 41 km from here to Rincon, 25 to Cacao, and 21 to Orosi. 360 Gigapan taken between 2 & 3. notes: Sift|Gnaptogenys at the colony entrance, Aphaenogaster, 2x Gnaptogenys, Myrmicinae|Traps out and bait down at 9am. Gigapan taken uphill from the creek under a fantastic canopy tree. notes: Bait|Attini, Myrmicinae, Gnaptogenys|20mEPE|Waypoint 191||1.25 hrs walk up to 970m (6:40 - 8:10). Traps out and bait down at 8:30 necessary to be back at 3:30 to leav safely and get gas in La Cruz. Rained all night and all morning on walk up - stopped at 9:00am though cloudy for the day (with wind). Large Eciton swarm came through at 10:20 and were on site until I departed. Filled and took over bait and traps at 2 and 3. Traps up and at 1:30. Malaise trap taken down. Page 131 in book. 360 GigaPan taken between 2 and 3 on trail.|http://www.gigapan.org/gigapans/66894/|http://bit.ly/eN2Flk|http://sites.google.com/site/acgdecembercollections/|

notes: Sift|Gnaptogenys at the colony entrance, Aphaenogaster, 2x Gnaptogenys, Myrmicinae|Traps out and bait down at 9am. Gigapan taken uphill from the creek under a fantastic canopy tree. Should be a Pachycondyla visible on the rock of the upstream direction. Temperature was 18-21C all day. Toledo birds singing after 12. 1 Agoti. Large ambulatory ponerinae and Gnaptogenys dominate here.
